<br>
How many more employees are they hiring more for the new premium server? Since we don't have any concrete numbers, let's assume that the number of new people they hired is the minimum needed for the premium server, and the $30 more that one has to pay is used to cover most of the cost of maintaining the new personnel with a small profit margin going to VI's pocket. This means that they would need also the same number of new personnel for all the existing servers if they want to provide the same things they plan for a premium server. So, even if they increase the basic subscription fee for everyone instead of having a premium server, they still wouldn't be able to offer to all servers what they now offer for the premium server. Unless that increase is also $30.<br>
<br>
Maybe that's why they decided to go with a premium server concept, instead of raising the price for everyone. <p>Thormiel Stormblade<BR>
